bib_record.title: Isotopic molybdenum total neutron cross section in the unresolved resonance region

free_txt: Data corrected for dead time (< 5%) and for
area of 910 cm2 and thickness of 1.27 cm. Glass
surface was perpendicular to neutron beam.
segments was read out using 8 photomultipliers,
located out of neutron beam. Detector was placed at
the distance of 88 m from the Mo sample
Neutrons were produced by 55 MeV electron
beam impinging on tantalum target. Repetition frequency
was 225 Hz and pulse width 12 ns. Water moderator
with diameter of 22.54 cm and thickness of 2.54 cm
was used. Nominal beam power was 1200 W.
Transmission method was used to determine
5.01 cm and nominal thickness of 0.381 cm, 0.03857 +-
0.00007 95Mo atoms/barn with total weight of 127.96 g
